and trigger a bulk download of these files to your local machine. Once the local project folder is ready, upload the files to a new private GitHub repository and deploy it as a Web Service on Render, ensuring the \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\" is configured in the Render dashboard environment variables for live AI analysis."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"258b2c55"},"source":["## Verify Local File Integrity\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Confirm that all 9 modular project files exist in the current Colab environment and provide a summary of their status.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"00ff3e3d"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","I will verify the presence of the 9 required modular project files using `os.path.exists()` and display their status in a formatted table to confirm the environment is ready for deployment.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"d1ce42fe","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776819950055,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":25,"user":{"displayName":"Syed Mehrab","userId":"10016417158375832621"}},"outputId":"3d3f50ca-2867-4608-ae18-6148f5feb677"},"source":["import os\n","\n","# Define the list of required project files\n","required_files = [\n","    'models.py',\n","    'prompts.py',\n","    'database.py',\n","    'tools.py',\n","    'agent.py',\n","    'requirements.txt',\n","    'app.py',\n","    'Procfile',\n","    'README.md'\n","]\n","\n","print(f\"{'File Name':<20} | {'Status':<10}\")\n","print(\"-\" * 33)\n","\n","# Iterate and check for each file's existence\n","for file_name in required_files:\n","    status = \"Found\" if os.path.exists(file_name) else \"MISSING\"\n","    print(f\"{file_name:<20} | {status:<10}\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["File Name            | Status    \n","---------------------------------\n","models.py            | Found     \n","prompts.py           | Found     \n","database.py          | Found     \n","tools.py             | Found     \n","agent.py             | Found     \n","requirements.txt     | Found     \n","app.py               | Found     \n","Procfile             | Found     \n","README.md            | Found     \n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"b6f31d7c"},"source":["## Private GitHub Repository Upload\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Prepare the project for a secure, private GitHub upload and provide instructions for repository initialization.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8fbb4ab0"},"source":["### 🔐 GitHub Upload & Security Guide\n","\n","Follow these steps to securely move your project from Colab to a private GitHub repository.\n","\n","#### 1. Security Audit\n","Before uploading, ensure your code handles keys safely. The project files generated (`app.py`, `agent.py`) are designed to use `os.getenv('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY')`.\n","\n","**Warning:** Never hardcode your actual API key string (e.g., `sk-ant...`) directly into any file you upload to GitHub.\n","\n","#### 2. Local Preparation\n","1. Create a new folder on your computer named `fx-trading-agent`.\n","2. Move all 9 downloaded files into this folder:\n","   - `models.py`, `prompts.py`, `database.py`, `tools.py`, `agent.py`\n","   - `requirements.txt`, `app.py`, `Procfile`, `README.md`\n","\n","#### 3. Initialize GitHub Repository\n","1. Go to [GitHub](https://github.com/new) and create a new repository.\n","2. **Name:** `fx-trading-agent`\n","3. **Visibility:** Select **Private** (Crucial for security).\n","4. Do **not** initialize with a README, license, or gitignore (we already have our files).\n","\n","#### 4. Uploading via Terminal\n","Open your terminal or command prompt inside your project folder and run:\n","\n","```bash\n","# Initialize git\n","git init\n","\n","# Stage all files\n","git add .\n","\n","# Create initial commit\n","git commit -m \"Initial production-ready commit\"\n","\n","# Link to your repository (Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your actual GitHub username)\n","git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/fx-trading-agent.git\n","\n","# Push to the main branch\n","git branch -M main\n","git push -u origin main\n","```"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"dd54ae3c"},"source":["## Render Web Service Connection\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Connect your GitHub repository to a new 'Web Service' on Render to initiate the cloud deployment.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ecbd1a13"},"source":["#### Instructions\n","1. Log in to your Render dashboard and click on the 'New +' button, then select 'Web Service'.\n","2. Connect your GitHub account and select the private 'fx-trading-agent' repository you just uploaded.\n","3. Configure the service with the following settings:\n","   - **Name**: `fx-trading-agent`\n","   - **Environment**: `Python 3` (or the latest available)\n","   - **Build Command**: `pip install -r requirements.txt`\n","   - **Start Command**: `gunicorn app:app`\n","4. Select the 'Free' instance type for testing or a paid tier for production stability, then click 'Create Web Service'.\n","5. Wait for the initial build to start, but note that it will likely fail or show an error until the API key environment variable is added in the next subtask."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"13c1cb7e"},"source":["## Configure Environment Variables\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Securely add the 'ANTHROPIC_API_KEY' to the Render dashboard to enable the Claude AI analysis in your production environment.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"faf9715a"},"source":["#### Instructions\n","1. In your Render dashboard, navigate to the 'Web Service' you just created for 'fx-trading-agent'.\n","2. Click on the 'Environment' tab in the left-hand sidebar.\n","3. Click the 'Add Environment Variable' button.\n","4. Enter 'ANTHROPIC_API_KEY' in the 'Key' field.\n","5. Paste your actual Anthropic API key (starting with 'sk-ant-...') into the 'Value' field.\n","6. Click 'Save Changes'. Render will automatically trigger a new deployment to apply the key.\n","7. Monitor the 'Events' or 'Logs' tab to confirm the service successfully redeploys and enters the 'Live' state."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"c2a938d5"},"source":["## Live Data Integration Check\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Confirm if the user wants to replace the simulated market data with a live production API key in `tools.py`.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ffc25d33"},"source":["### 📡 Live Data Integration Overview\n","\n","The current implementation in `tools.py` uses simulated (mock) data for OHLCV prices and technical indicators to facilitate testing and development without requiring external costs.\n","\n","#### Steps for Production Integration:\n","1. **Sign Up**: Register with a market data provider such as [Twelve Data](https://twelvedata.com/) or OANDA to obtain a production-grade API key.\n","2. **Modify `tools.py`**: Update the `fetch_ohlcv` and `gather_market_context` functions. Replace the simulated dictionaries with `requests.get()` calls to the provider's REST endpoints.\n","3. **Environment Configuration**: Add your new API key (e.g., `TWELVE_DATA_API_KEY`) to your Render Dashboard under **Environment Variables**. This keeps your keys secure and out of the source code.\n","4. **Update `agent.py`**: Ensure the `TWELVE_DATA_KEY` variable correctly pulls from `os.getenv('TWELVE_DATA_API_KEY')`.\n","\n","By integrating a live API, the agent will analyze real-time volatility and price action, providing authentic trading signals."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"31f27f54"},"source":["## Final Task\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Summarize the deployment readiness and provide final guidance on accessing the live production URL.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a1086ac7"},"source":["## Summary:\n","\n","### Q&A\n","\n","**Which files are required for the modular project deployment?**\n","The 9 required files are `models.py`, `prompts.py`, `database.py`, `tools.py`, `agent.py`, `requirements.txt`, `app.py`, `Procfile`, and `README.md`.\n","\n","**How is the Anthropic API key handled for security?**\n","The project uses `os.getenv('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY')` to retrieve credentials from the environment. Users are instructed to add this key in the Render dashboard's \"Environment\" tab rather than hardcoding it into the source files.\n","\n","### Data Analysis Key Findings\n","\n","*   **File Integrity Verified**: A local environment check confirmed that all 9 modular project files exist and are ready for deployment.\n","*   **Production Configuration**: The deployment on Render requires specific settings:\n","    *   **Build Command**: `pip install -r requirements.txt`\n","    *   **Start Command**: `gunicorn app:app`\n","    *   **Environment**: Python 3\n","*   **Security Protocol**: To prevent credential leaks, the workflow enforces a private GitHub repository and the use of environment variables for the `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`.\n","*   **Live Data Readiness**: The current system uses mock data in `tools.py`. Transitioning to production requires replacing simulated functions with REST API calls to providers like Twelve Data or OANDA.\n","\n","### Insights or Next Steps\n","\n","*   **Finalize Live Deployment**: After uploading the code to a private GitHub repository, connect it to a Render Web Service and input the `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` to trigger the final build.\n","*   **Transition to Real Data**: Replace the simulated market data in `tools.py` with live API integrations and add the corresponding provider keys to Render’s environment variables to enable real-time trading signals.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"1b8927cb"},"source":["### 📡 Live Data Integration Overview\n","\n","The current implementation in `tools.py` uses simulated (mock) data for OHLCV prices and technical indicators to facilitate testing and development without requiring external costs.\n","\n","#### Steps for Product